text.section:
Compensation shall be paid for the period listed for the loss of the following:
a thumb, 100 weeks;
a 1st finger, commonly called the index finger, 40 weeks;
a 2nd finger, 35 weeks;
a 3rd finger, 30 weeks;
a 4th finger, commonly called the little finger, 25 weeks; and
a great toe, 40 weeks.

section.section:
Compensation shall be paid for the period listed for the loss of the following:
1 of the toes other than the great toe, 10 weeks;
a hand, 250 weeks;
an arm, 300 weeks;
a foot, 250 weeks;
a leg, 300 weeks; and
an eye, 250 weeks.
